> activate portal

> activate portal
You have correctly ordered the constellations. The portal widens and a rift opens from its center. Your body rockets into the portal, and everything goes dark.

You open your eyes and find yourself back in the Medical Station. Ziggy and Duffy  are in exactly the same position as they were when you touched the device. Wherever you were - whatever just happened - must have transpired in an instant, here.

The strange device has disappeared.

You are in a Makeshift alien medical station.
You can see Ziggy, Duffy, an Alien Supply Crate (containing a Hacking tool, a Disruptor, a Foresight and a Cryocharge) and a laser.

After examining your surroundings for a moment, you are sure that you've returned to the Medical Station, and that nothing has changed. However, you find something cold in your pocket. You reach inside and pull out a pulsing blue orb, around the size of a marble. It wasn't in your pocket before you touched the strange device. You aren't sure what it does, but it might be worth keeping.
You can go north.
> north

> north

You are in an entrance to the Medical Station.
You can see Duffy, Ziggy and a busted time capsule.
You exit the Medical Station and see the world for the first time in over a hundred years.

You wonder, for a moment, if the aliens are decieving you. Perhaps they took you to thier own world. Maybe this isn't Earth.

But you see the decaying remains of office buildings; vines cascade over each floor, and into the broken broken windows, like water pouring over the cells in a honeycomb.

A large tree sits in the middle of a nearby street, having pierced the hitch of a truck, splitting tractor from trailer.

The verdent landscape reminds you of deep-jungle plateaus, with ancient indian temples built into the mountain sides; starved out by new growth.

The dizzy sensation returns. but you quickly shake it and continue.
You can go south or north.
> look at busted time capsule

> look at busted time capsule
This time capsule recently busted open. Possibly during the alien's excavation of my stasis chamber. There are a few items of interest scattered around it. I should take a look at them. Something might be useful.
> take cell phone

> take cell phone
(Phone placed in inventory)
"I found an old cell phone," you say, turning to the aliens. "It looks like it could still work."
"Let me see that," Duffy replies. "With a little reprogramming, this could be a valuable interface with any human technology we encounter."

Duffy presses a button on his wrist device, which begins scanning the phone. Suddenly, the phone bursts to life and begins its start-up sequence. He hands the device back to me.

"Reprogramming..." he pauses for a moment," successful. Hold on to it. We might need it."
