You can go north, northwest or south.
> north

> north
You catch a glimpse of something ahead, darting around a street corner. It disappears as quickly as you saw it. After a gurgling screech, its prescence quickly fades.

You associate its size with that of a bear; although you are sure it was not actually a bear.

Ziggy says to Duffy, "You're prepared, right?"

Duffy replies, "That assumes I know what we're up against."

 City Streets (Challenging Pathway).
You can see Duffy, Ziggy, a bone fragment, a massive skeleton and a street sign.
You proceed into the streets of a ruined city. The buildings warp and buckle under the crushing weight of time and deterioration. Rubble blocks sections of the street and building entrances.

Something in particular catches your eye. A massive skeleton of some unknown creature lies in the interesection ahead. It looks to be fragmented, with a few missing pieces. It's enourmous; almost dinosaur in size.

It looks as if your path forward lies over or around this skeleton. But there's something strange about the ground it lies on.

You notice sparks. The skeleton is lying on a bed of live wires. Somehow, the wires are still electrified. That mystery, for the moment, is secondary to finding a way to cross.
You can go west, east or north.
> east

> east

You are by a tank sitting on the curb.
You can see a tank and a bone fragment.
It's some derelict combat tank. The main cannon's barrel is bent downward. something must have fallen on it, to be warped like that, but there is no debris around the vehicle.

You don't recognize the type, but there's probably a mark or flag, for the country of origin. That might help you narrow down where you are. Who knows what things you might remember after you can nail down your location?
You can go west.
