You've crossed the skeleton and are in a smalll courtyard.

To your left is a thrift store. Years of sunlight and weather have bleached the letters and worn them down to near-nothing, requiring you to afford more than a glance to read them. It says, "esmond's Pawn Shop". The first letter is missing. Probably a "D".

Straight ahead against a building wall, are solar panels and a generator, sitting under a short metal roof.

