> look at control panel

> look at control panel
The northwest door doesn't have a label, but it is the only door in the hallway with a special locking mechanism. On the mechanism is a single button, and a speaker. The speaker device appears to be if high quality, and seems like it would still work. The device is presumably powered, as a very light static noise is coming from the speaker.
> open binder

> open binder
You open it.
Most of the laminated manual pages have been discarded somewhere. There's one page in the binder.
It contains a Robotics Control Manual.
> look at Robotics Control Manual

> look at Robotics Control Manual
It is a control manual for "Manual Activation Robotic Specialists (MARS)". Much of the page was destroyed or masked with a dark ink. The readable sections say,

"All PERSA reactors have a 'Robotics Room' where Manual Activation Robotic Specialists (MARS) are stored. These tools are critcally useful in the event of a miscommunication in remote instructions to the reactor core. Each MARS can be controlled remotely via a terminal located in a facility control room. Location and security clearance of control rooms vary with each facility."
