> activate computer terminal

> activate computer terminal

The computer requests a password.

(Enter the password now)
> LIFE86Z0J

The computer accepts your password, and boots to a control panel. The control panel describes the core functionality.

Apparently, this computer activates and controls robotic maitenance drones. These drones negate the dangerous nature of working in a radioactive environment, and allow the user to interface with the reactor in a manual way, while still being in a remote location. There is a warning displayed at the bottom of the screen. It says,

"Per AOSA guidlines, section 3.34 - in the event of a breakdown in direct remote communication with the reactor, certified engineers may use robotics to manually interface with the reactor."

A command line is displayed on the console. It says, "Type 'Activate MARS' to begin."
